      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum FEA with nonlinear geometry and frictional contact is appropriate for quasi-static compression-bending of metallic implant constructs; model form uncertainty quantified via literature comparison.",
      "rationale": "Continuum FEA with large-displacement formulation and penalty-based frictional contact (mu=0.2) is well-established for metallic spinal implant simulation. Model form uncertainty estimated at ±5% based on literature survey of comparable pedicle screw FEA studies. Bilinear isotropic hardening material model for Ti-6Al-4V validated against published coupon test data."
